                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-03-26T11:00:46.084-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>“You have Parkinson’s.” These three words changed Cathy Molohan’s life forever. At 38, she was already navigating the complexities of everyday life as a wife, mother, and business owner. Suddenly, she faced the daunting impact of her diagnosis.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Despite the challenges she faced, Molohan found resilience, “While Parkinson’s has slowed me, it hasn’t stopped me,” she shares. “It's taught me to listen to my body and to take care of myself because my body gets revenge on me if I don’t.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Today, simple tasks, like rising from a chair, sometimes require the helping hands of her children. The everyday trials and triumphs in her journey highlight the reality faced by millions living with this chronic, progressive neurological disorder.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <image_copy
                                jcr:created="{Date}2025-03-26T11:00:59.374-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-03-28T14:30:20.683-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/image/v2/image"
                                altValueFromDAM="true"
                                displayPopupTitle="true"
                                dmPresetType="imagePreset"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/parkinsons-disease-community/abbreviated-spark-the-night-infographic.svg"
                                isDecorative="false"
                                openInNewWindow="false"
                                titleValueFromDAM="true"/>
                            <container4_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756486159]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2025-03-26T11:40:00.777-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-03-26T11:40:00.777-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-03-28T09:53:21.518-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>For over 20 years, AbbVie has invested heavily in exploring ways to reduce the burdens of Parkinson’s disease for patients like Molohan, recognizing the need for therapies that not only address its symptoms, but disease progression at its core.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“While the nature of the disease means that there is often no ‘one-size-fits-all’ approach to treating symptoms, we aim to meet the unique needs of those living with Parkinson’s disease, ranging from symptomatic to disease modifying approaches,” explains Jan Stoehr, Ph.D., head of Parkinson's disease biology, neuroscience discovery research at AbbVie.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Despite progress, challenges remain, such as lack of reliable biomarkers that can measure disease progression and how a patient may respond to treatment. Furthermore, current disease models often fail to accurately replicate human disease, impacting the reliability of treatment testing.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>AbbVie&amp;nbsp;is leveraging its legacy in Parkinson’s disease to tackle these challenges. Its teams are focused on unraveling the molecular and genetic changes within cells leading to the onset and progression of the disease.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy>
                            <quote_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2022-11-16T17:03:32.882-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-03-28T09:53:39.794-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Jan Stoehr Ph.D."
                                attributionTitle="Head of Parkinson's Disease Biology, Neuroscience Discovery Research at AbbVie"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/parkinsons-disease-community/jan-stoehr-headshot.jpg"
                                quote="While our ultimate goal is to cure Parkinson's disease, we recognize that this is not easily achievable. What is within reach is the ability to slow progression of disease."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-03-28T09:55:50.975-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Additionally, the company is advancing the discovery of novel biomarkers, disease models and cutting-edge imaging to enable early diagnosis, track progression, and evaluate treatment efficacy. Through these efforts, AbbVie aims to develop innovative therapies that may improve the quality of life for those living with Parkinson’s disease.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We understand that we can't achieve this alone—it will require a collective effort from across the industry, academia and non-profit organizations in the global fight against Parkinson's,” adds Stoehr.&lt;b>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>For Molohan, who was born in Ireland and now resides in Germany, she sees the need for global advocacy to address the many challenges those living with Parkinson’s disease face. She was instrumental in launching the first ever &lt;a href=&quot;https://parkinsonseurope.org/app/uploads/2024/11/Call-to-Action-Enhancing-Parkinsons-Care-in-Europe_FINAL.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Parkinson’s disease call to action&lt;/a> in Europe late last year.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“I feel very strongly about actively raising European voices, in addition to U.S. ones,” Molohan shares. “The problems we're trying to solve require a wide audience. We need everyone onboard and united in the call to action.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
